From c3fd0514a45fb79096105c64205ae98cd607755e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Bryant <david@wavpack.com>
Date: Wed, 12 Feb 2025 15:58:40 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] src/unpack_utils.c: fix for multiple oss-fuzz issues

- issue 395207094, Heap-use-after-free in unpack_dsd_samples
- issue 394980079, Use-of-uninitialized-value in get_words_lossless
- issue 395669934, Null-dereference READ in unpack_dsd_samples
- all issues were manifestations of the same multithreading bug
  (attempting to decode more samples from an exhausted block)
- no stack or writes involved, so not serious vulnerabilities
- the NULL-dereference causes an exception, but could only cause
  a DoS if running as a web service (which I've never heard of)
- trigger files added to regression test
